{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh water, ¾ tsp salt and livers into it. Set bowl aside and allow livers to soak for 30 minutes. Drain livers and discard salted water.","Place bay leaf, peppercorns, Riesling and drained livers into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>10-12 min\/80°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until livers are cooked. Transfer livers into simmering basket and set aside to drain. Discard cooking liquid.","Place cooked livers, butter, port or cognac, 1 tsp salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>20-30 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>, or until a mousse consistency is achieved.","Transfer into a terrine or ramekin (350 ml capacity) and refrigerate for a minimum 2 hours. Serve with toasted bread."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g water","1 tsp sea salt, plus an extra 3\/4 tsp for soaking","250 g duck livers","½ dried bay leaf","6 whole black peppercorns","150 g Riesling","180 g salted butter, softened, cut into pieces","1 tbsp port","&frac18; tsp freshly ground black pepper","bread, toasted, to serve"]}],"id":"r99024","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-bcWUBjwVJG4\/XZMuPgH5AMI\/AAAAAAAAaDA\/-rIOY2_k5ucLFtEgYVi56w7xiCnX1yTKQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ENMuRiyLwkCskBQR.png","title":"Pâtè with Riesling","publishedAt":"2015-08-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.5 g","fat":"27 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1 g","calories":"1194 kJ \/ 284 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, terrine, refrigerator","basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h","6 portions"]}